This statement by the President commemorates the 20th anniversary of the Srebrenica genocide, expressing mourning for the over 8,000 victims and honoring those still being laid to rest or missing. It reflects on the tragedy of Srebrenica, where many were killed in the largest massacre in Europe in 50 years, and emphasizes the importance of acknowledging the past, holding the perpetrators accountable, and calling out evil to achieve true reconciliation and justice. It also highlights how the international community was mobilized by the tragedy to end the war and commits the United States to continue helping heal the wounds of the past in partnership with Balkan countries.